n's experiences with youth participation—ranging from digital citizenship initiatives to the voices of community media to the beats of hip hop culture—to show how young people can be at the forefront of fostering ecologies of artistic and grassroots engagement in order to reshape civic life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCommunicationxPolitical aspectszColombiazMedellín. 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspectszColombiazMedellín. 0aMass media and youthzColombiazMedellín. 0aSocial mediazColombiazMedellín. 0aYouthxPolitical activityzColombiazMedellín. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  acontemporary digital culture.  aparticipatory public cultures.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478009085zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478009085423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478009085/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020